(firstQuint)Videoendoscopic Pilonidal Sinus Surgery.

 Lots of surgical techniques are performing on pilonidal sinus disease treatment.

 Lately large flap techniques are popular but causing anatomical distortions and bad cosmesis.

 In this new approach the investigators concluded that two 1cm diameter holes are enough to surgical treatment.

 One hole is for videoendoscopic camera and the other one for grasper to extract piluses and granulation tissues.

